==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic: cognate with Old Frisian [[aka|āka]], Old Saxon [[okian|ōkian]], Old Norse [[auka]], Gothic [[𐌰𐌿𐌺𐌰𐌽]].  From the same Indo-European source as Latin [[augere]], Greek [[αυχειν]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'æ:akan/

===Verb===
'''ēacan'''
# to be increased or enlarged

===Descendants===
*English [[eke]]
*Scots [[eik]]

